5:
Goddamn, how many of these guys
are there? They won't stop comin'.
8:
Kinda starting to wish our
instructions weren't to clear out
everything on the mountain...
12:
Focus, both of you! Aim your attacks
at the same target and―
17: The hell was that? An explosion?
37:
Well, consider yourselves
lucky―Botan is here to save the day!
40:
I'll blow all these stupid yokai
sky-high! Hyaaaaaaaa!
52:
Everyone all right? No one hurt? If so,
let's head on down to―
58:
Whoa, whoa, whoa! And here I
thought you were humans―you
some kind of shape-shifting yokai?
64: Cause if you are, I swear I'll shoot!
69: No no no! We're not yokai!
75:
Oh. My bad! I guess I jumped to the
wrong conclusion there!
78:
Iunno if it's much of an apology, but
feel free to catch a breather here
and maybe have some tea!
81:
But uh, don't touch any of the stuff
over there. Lots of gunpowder, you
never know when it might go BOOM!
85:
Is it really wise to store such
dangerous materials here? What
exactly do you do, Botan?
90:
I'm what you'd call a pyrotechnician,
duh! This is my humble workshop.
92:
I happened to be out gatherin'
compounds for my fireworks when I
came across those yokai you were
fightin'.
96:
Fireworks! No wonder they were
super pretty!
100:
Hah! Keep the compliments coming,
please!
102:
But to tell you the truth, the ones
back there were all defective! I was
just gettin' rid of them. The coloring
was all wrong!
106:
Oof, it's honestly a cryin' shame, but
I'll be real here: I'm in a bit of a jam
at the moment.
109:
You guys are... adventurers, 
I gather?
It ain't easy but I guess I'll swallow
my pride and just ask...
112:
If you find any good compounds I
could make use of, would you be
willin' to help a gal out and pass 'em
on to me?
116:
It is certainly a most sudden
request. What kind of compounds
did you have in mind?
121:
It don't matter! Anything that could
add a splash of color would work.
I'm not ruling anything out.
137:
This rock... could I have it? Or, wait, I'll
buy it from you! Please!
144:
Really? Okay, okay, then park
yourselves here for a moment! I'll be
back.
151:
All right, sorry to make you wait! Let's
test this baby out!
154:
You already made fireworks from
that stone we gave you? That was
fast!
157:
Oh, it's no biggie. Just gotta check
the coloration before throwing it
together!
170: All that just 'cause of a tiny rock?
174:
So... Was that the kinda thing you
were looking for?
187:
This color! I've never seen anything
like it before!
193:
You absolutely HAVE to tell
me—where on earth did you get
that rock?!
198:
Huh, so you used this ... Word
Flapper thing?
202:
World Flipper, yes. It'll be hard to get
you more of those rocks locally.
205:
Well that don't bother me! I'll just join
up with you and visit these other
worlds!
210:
Is that really something you can
decide so flippantly? What of your
job, or your family?
213:
Family? I do have a father, but he
works in a different workshop. Ain't
seen him in years!
220:
Let's just say we don't see eye to
eye! And that I occasionally wanna
sock him right in the face.
224:
Meaning, I have no issues with
leaving! Please take me with you!
230:
This might be a curiosity killed the
cat situation, but I do wanna see
what kinda fireworks you whip up
next!
241:
I can't believe I'm headin' to a totally
new world! What kinda fireworks can
I make over there, I wonder?
